node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 16, 2021 tagging @farawaypoetry. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'My favorite season will always be the one we met in. -faraway'.

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 16, 2021 tagging @christianweissmann. May be an image of text that says 'MI THE LOVER over the past few years i've cried hundreds of tears counted thousands of regrets and longed for love that millions want but few ever achieve looking for permanent fulfillment in temporary lovers tarot card videos and empty whiskey bottles the search for extrinsic meaning is a journey set sail on years ago and i'm scared to jump ship -christian weissmann VII'.

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 16, 2021 tagging @seydanoirwords. May be an image of text that says 'love is quite astonishing like that, it invites us in to make a home, so special that we are already trying to rebuild it before it's finished burning down. şeyda noir'.

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 16, 2021 tagging @haleymacleod. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'pay attention to what kind of light you become around people - hold onto the ones who start wildfires of passion within your heart and let go of the ones who make you feel like you are living in darkness. -haley macLeod'.

node.text:
Don't be afraid to let go of people that no longer bring out the best in you. ⚡️⠀
(cr: @haleymacleod)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 16, 2021 tagging @clareguintu. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'You call me cruel After I finally chose To love myself fully Before you -clare guintu'.

node.text:
Are you putting yourself first right now? ☕️⠀
(cr: @clareguintu)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 15, 2021 tagging @rafpoetry. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'In times of all kinds of uncertainty and worry... I wish upon you strength and courage. May you conquer every challenge. raf'.

node.text:
I wish upon you strength and courage.⠀
(cr: @rafpoetry)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 15, 2021 tagging @atishbaazi_. May be an image of text that says 'I always wanted you to be a part of my book But you ended up becoming my my whole damn story. -Atish Chintalwar'.
Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 15, 2021 tagging @flower__poetry. May be an image of text that says 'Ûe Those you have loved deeply will forever remain alive in your heart.'.

node.text:
Gone doesn't have to mean forgotten 💫 ⠀
Follow @flower__poetry for more beautiful thoughts

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 15, 2021 tagging @bergan.behr. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'Sweet girl, Your past does not define you Your mistakes are not who you are You are loved You are seen You are enough B.Ð'.

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 15, 2021 tagging @d.m__poetry. May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'You can paint whatever picture you would like of me, but that will only be your version of what you see... it took me years to re-paint my own image, trading shadows for sunlight, beauty from the ashes of the old me, and that is the true masterpiece, and will always be beautiful, even if your canvas of me holds no color at all. all @d.m_poetry'.

node.text:
The way you see yourself is so important 🐚⠀
(cr: @d.m__poetry)
